            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind Letter &amp; presents which I dare
                    say will arrive in good time. I am much obliged to you for the offer of
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0149">Adairs maps</title></bibl> but I have them. I know nothing of Skinnerâ€™s outline of
                    the Highlands,<note type="editorial">Possibly the preliminary 'A General Map of
                        the Roads' from <bibl>Taylor and Skinner's <title ref="bi0186"><hi rend="italic">Survey and maps of the roads of North Britain or
                                    Scotland</hi></title> (London: 1776)</bibl>.</note> but will
                    write to <persName ref="pe0006">Bailey</persName> about. I am sorry to see He has made
                    no use of it. Is there no news yet from <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dr Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T. Pennant</persName></signed>

                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> July 18<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1777.</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>Pray excuse the inclosed</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
